<h2>ingredients</h2>
<ul>
  <li>300g butter</li>
  <li>4dl sugar</li>
  <li>4tbsp syrup</li>
  <li>4teaspoon vanilla sugar</li>
  <li>3 eggs</li>
  <li>7dl wheat flour</li>
  <li>1tbsp bicarbonate 3tbsp baking powder</li>
  <li>1pinch of salt</li>
  <li>150-200g chocolate chips/</li>
</ul>

<h2>instructions</h2>
<ol>
  <li>Preheat oven to 175°c</li>
  <li>Beat toghether the butter sugar syrup and vanilla sugar into a fluffy batter</li>
  <li>Add the eggs while still whisking, one by one</li>
  <li>In a seperate bowl carefully mix ur wheat floar bicarbonate and salt</li>
  <li>add the dry ingredients to the other bowl and mix gently with a spatula until u have a smoof and stiky dough</li>
  <li>finally add the chokolate chips and mux gently until evenly distributed</li>
  <li>let dough rest for 30 mins before rolling it into 36 equal balls and distributing them on baking sheets covered with baking paper. Press them down lightly and keep a good distance between the cookies on the sheet so that they don't melt together in the oven.</li>
  <li>Bake the cookies in the lower part of the oven for about 10 minutes. They should be just cooked around the edges and still soft in the middle.</li>
  <li>Once you have removed the cookies from the oven, immediately transfer the baking paper with the cookies onto a wire rack to cool.</li>
  <li>If they remain on the hot baking sheet, they will be baked with residual heat and lose their good chewiness in the middle.</li>
  <li>Let cool thoroughly before serving!</li>
</ol>

